<title>USA: MCA to buy 50 percent of Polish TV station.</title>
<headline>MCA to buy 50 percent of Polish TV station.</headline>
<dateline>UNIVERSAL CITY, Calif.</dateline>
<text>
<p>MCA Inc. said Thursday it reached an agreement to buy a 50 percent stake in Luxembourg-based media group CLT's RTL7, the free, satellite-and cable-delivered general entertainment local language channel in Poland.</p>
<p>RTL7 is scheduled to launch Dec. 7. Terms of the deal were not released.</p>
<p>In a statement, MCA said it will provide both first-run and library programming, and will create two Universal branded programming blocks, consisting of movie and action- adventure themes.</p>
<p>First-run titles will include, &quot;Beethoven,&quot; &quot;The Burning Zone,&quot; &quot;Coach&quot; and &quot;EZ Streets,&quot; among others. Feature length titles will include &quot;Airport,&quot; &quot;The Land Before Time,&quot; &quot;Dead Men Don't Wear Plaid,&quot; and more.</p>
